text: The 1916 Tempe Normal Owls football team was an American football team that represented Tempe Normal School (later renamed Arizona State University) as an independent during the 1916 college football season. In their third and final season under head coach George Schaeffer, the Owls compiled a 0–3 record and were outscored by their opponents by a combined total of 51 to 13. Archie Ivy was the team captain. ==References== Tempe Normal Category:Arizona State Sun Devils football seasons Category:College football winless seasons Category:1916 in Arizona
